race.description: In Memory Of Anthea Wright Hcp (C1)
race.comment: DEEL ME A QUEEN (4) returned after a year off the scene with a dogged maiden win over 1400m at Scone last start. Four-year-old who has had her issues and lines up for only the third time today. Thought she may be looking for further now but still looks the one they have to beat. Kris Lees' mare KHAMIS (5) is back from a 19-week spell. Didn't live up to expectations last prep but wet tracks may have been to blame - the best rating of five came on the only good track she faced. Should be ready to run well. TILLSTROM (1) started favourite on debut last start over 1400m at Grafton and had to dig deep to get the prize. Did race a bit keenly that day so the blinkers come off. Can improve and play a big role again. RASLOC (9) gets a pass mark for her first-up fourth over 1200m at Cootamundra. Looks ready for this longer journey now. OUR EMILY (6) has struggled of late but in a thin race can sneak into the top four.
